newsitem.title: USA: CBOT soy products close lower as soybeans drop.
newsitem.headline: CBOT soy products close lower as soybeans drop.

text.p: CBOT soy product futures closed lower on a drop in soybeans triggered by technical fund selling, traders said.
The September soymeal contract dragged the market down and expired sharply lower at $266.30 per ton, down $8.60. September soyoil expired 0.05 cent per lb higher at 25.20.
Soymeal futures volume was estimated at 35,000 contracts, up from 30,322 Wednesday, according to the CBOT. Soyoil futures volume was estimated at 20,000 contracts, up from 18,491 Wednesday.
Soymeal closed $2.80 per ton lower to $1.00 higher, with October down $2.80 at $258.70.
Soyoil closed 0.14 to 0.22 cent per lb lower, with October down 0.14 at 25.06.
